comment: * Configs used for epdg tunnel bring up. * * @see RFC 7296, Internet Key Exchange Protocol * Version 2 (IKEv2)

variables.name: KEY_PREFIX
variables.comment: Prefix of all Epdg.KEY_* constants.

variables.name: KEY_CHILD_SA_REKEY_HARD_TIMER_SEC_INT
variables.comment:
* Time in seconds after which the child security association session is terminated if rekey
         * procedure is not successful. If not set or set to <= 0, the default value is 3600
         * seconds.

variables.name: KEY_CHILD_SA_REKEY_SOFT_TIMER_SEC_INT
variables.comment:
* Time in seconds after which the child session rekey procedure is started. If not set or
         * set to <= 0, default value is 3000 seconds.

variables.name: KEY_DIFFIE_HELLMAN_GROUPS_INT_ARRAY
variables.comment:
* Supported DH groups for IKE negotiation. Possible values are:
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#DH_GROUP_NONE},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#DH_GROUP_1024_BIT_MODP},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#DH_GROUP_1536_BIT_MODP},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#DH_GROUP_2048_BIT_MODP},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#DH_GROUP_3072_BIT_MODP},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#DH_GROUP_4096_BIT_MODP}

variables.name: KEY_DPD_TIMER_SEC_INT
variables.comment:
* Time in seconds after which a dead peer detection (DPD) request is sent. If not set or
         * set to <= 0, default value is 120 seconds.

variables.name: KEY_EPDG_AUTHENTICATION_METHOD_INT
variables.comment:
* Method used to authenticate epdg server. Possible values are {@link
         * #AUTHENTICATION_METHOD_EAP_ONLY}, {@link #AUTHENTICATION_METHOD_CERT}

variables.name: KEY_EPDG_ADDRESS_PRIORITY_INT_ARRAY
KEY_EPDG_PLMN_PRIORITY_INT_ARRAY
variables.comment:
* A priority list of PLMN to be used in EPDG_ADDRESS_PLMN. Possible values are {@link
         * #EPDG_PLMN_RPLMN}, {@link #EPDG_PLMN_HPLMN}, {@link #EPDG_PLMN_EHPLMN_ALL}, {@link
         * #EPDG_PLMN_EHPLMN_FIRST}
         *
         * @hide

variables.name: KEY_EPDG_STATIC_ADDRESS_STRING
variables.comment: Epdg static IP address or FQDN

variables.name: KEY_EPDG_STATIC_ADDRESS_ROAMING_STRING
variables.comment: Epdg static IP address or FQDN for roaming

variables.name: KEY_SUPPORTS_IKE_SESSION_MULTIPLE_SA_PROPOSALS_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Enables the use of multiple IKE SA proposals, encompassing both carrier-preferred
         * ciphers and all supported ciphers from 3GPP TS 33.210 and RFC 8221,
         * as defined in RFC 7296.

variables.name: KEY_SUPPORTS_CHILD_SESSION_MULTIPLE_SA_PROPOSALS_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Enables the use of multiple Child SA proposals, encompassing both carrier-preferred
         * ciphers and all supported ciphers from 3GPP TS 33.210 and RFC 8221,
         * as defined in RFC 7296.

variables.name: KEY_CHILD_SESSION_AES_CBC_KEY_SIZE_INT_ARRAY
variables.comment:
* List of supported key sizes for AES Cipher Block Chaining (CBC) encryption mode of child
         * session. Possible values are:
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#KEY_LEN_UNUSED},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#KEY_LEN_AES_128},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#KEY_LEN_AES_192},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#KEY_LEN_AES_256}

variables.name: KEY_CHILD_SESSION_AES_CTR_KEY_SIZE_INT_ARRAY
variables.comment:
* List of supported key sizes for AES Counter (CTR) encryption mode of child session.
         * Possible values are:
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#KEY_LEN_UNUSED},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#KEY_LEN_AES_128},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#KEY_LEN_AES_192},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#KEY_LEN_AES_256}

variables.name: KEY_CHILD_SESSION_AES_GCM_KEY_SIZE_INT_ARRAY
variables.comment:
* List of supported key sizes for AES Galois/Counter Mode (GCM) encryption mode
         * of child session.
         * Possible values are:
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#KEY_LEN_UNUSED},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#KEY_LEN_AES_128},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#KEY_LEN_AES_192},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#KEY_LEN_AES_256}

variables.name: KEY_SUPPORTED_CHILD_SESSION_ENCRYPTION_ALGORITHMS_INT_ARRAY
KEY_SUPPORTED_CHILD_SESSION_AEAD_ALGORITHMS_INT_ARRAY
variables.comment:
* List of supported AEAD algorithms for child session. Possible values are
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#ENCRYPTION_ALGORITHM_AES_GCM_8},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#ENCRYPTION_ALGORITHM_AES_GCM_12},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#ENCRYPTION_ALGORITHM_AES_GCM_16}

variables.name: KEY_IKE_REKEY_HARD_TIMER_SEC_INT
variables.comment:
* Time in seconds after which the IKE session is terminated if rekey procedure is not
         * successful. If not set or set to <= 0, default value is 3600 seconds.

variables.name: KEY_IKE_REKEY_SOFT_TIMER_SEC_INT
variables.comment:
* Time in seconds after which the IKE session rekey procedure is started. If not set or set
         * to <= 0, default value is 3000 seconds.

variables.name: KEY_IKE_SESSION_AES_CBC_KEY_SIZE_INT_ARRAY
variables.comment:
* List of supported key sizes for AES Cipher Block Chaining (CBC) encryption mode of IKE
         * session. Possible values:
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#KEY_LEN_UNUSED},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#KEY_LEN_AES_128},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#KEY_LEN_AES_192},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#KEY_LEN_AES_256}

variables.name: KEY_IKE_SESSION_AES_CTR_KEY_SIZE_INT_ARRAY
variables.comment:
* List of supported key sizes for AES Counter (CTR) encryption mode of IKE session.
         * Possible values -
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#KEY_LEN_UNUSED},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#KEY_LEN_AES_128},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#KEY_LEN_AES_192},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#KEY_LEN_AES_256}

variables.name: KEY_IKE_SESSION_AES_GCM_KEY_SIZE_INT_ARRAY
variables.comment:
* List of supported key sizes for AES Galois/Counter Mode (GCM) encryption mode
         * of IKE session.
         * Possible values -
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#KEY_LEN_UNUSED},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#KEY_LEN_AES_128},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#KEY_LEN_AES_192},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#KEY_LEN_AES_256}

variables.name: KEY_SUPPORTED_IKE_SESSION_ENCRYPTION_ALGORITHMS_INT_ARRAY
KEY_SUPPORTED_IKE_SESSION_AEAD_ALGORITHMS_INT_ARRAY
variables.comment:
* List of supported AEAD algorithms for IKE session. Possible values are
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#ENCRYPTION_ALGORITHM_AES_GCM_8},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#ENCRYPTION_ALGORITHM_AES_GCM_12},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#ENCRYPTION_ALGORITHM_AES_GCM_16}

variables.name: KEY_SUPPORTED_INTEGRITY_ALGORITHMS_INT_ARRAY
variables.comment:
* List of supported integrity algorithms for IKE session. Possible values are
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#INTEGRITY_ALGORITHM_NONE},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#INTEGRITY_ALGORITHM_HMAC_SHA1_96},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#INTEGRITY_ALGORITHM_AES_XCBC_96},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#INTEGRITY_ALGORITHM_HMAC_SHA2_256_128},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#INTEGRITY_ALGORITHM_HMAC_SHA2_384_192},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#INTEGRITY_ALGORITHM_HMAC_SHA2_512_256}

variables.name: KEY_MAX_RETRIES_INT
variables.comment: Maximum number of retries for tunnel establishment.

variables.name: KEY_NATT_KEEP_ALIVE_TIMER_SEC_INT
variables.comment:
* Time in seconds after which a NATT keep alive message is sent. If not set or set to <= 0,
         * default value is 20 seconds.

variables.name: KEY_MCC_MNCS_STRING_ARRAY
variables.comment: List of '-' separated MCC/MNCs used to create ePDG FQDN as per 3GPP TS 23.003

variables.name: KEY_SUPPORTED_PRF_ALGORITHMS_INT_ARRAY
variables.comment:
* List of supported pseudo random function algorithms for IKE session. Possible values are
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#PSEUDORANDOM_FUNCTION_HMAC_SHA1},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#PSEUDORANDOM_FUNCTION_AES128_XCBC},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#PSEUDORANDOM_FUNCTION_SHA2_256},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#PSEUDORANDOM_FUNCTION_SHA2_384},
         * {@link android.net.ipsec.ike.SaProposal#PSEUDORANDOM_FUNCTION_SHA2_512}

variables.name: KEY_RETRANSMIT_TIMER_MSEC_INT_ARRAY
variables.comment:
* List of IKE message retransmission timeouts in milliseconds, where each timeout
         * is the waiting time before next retry, except the last timeout which is the waiting time
         * before terminating the IKE Session. Min list length = 1, Max
         * list length = 10 Min timeout = 500 ms, Max timeout = 1800000 ms

variables.name: KEY_IKE_LOCAL_ID_TYPE_INT
variables.comment:
* Specifies the local identity type for IKE negotiations. Possible values are {@link
         * #ID_TYPE_FQDN}, {@link #ID_TYPE_RFC822_ADDR}, {@link #ID_TYPE_KEY_ID}

variables.name: KEY_IKE_REMOTE_ID_TYPE_INT
variables.comment:
* Specifies the remote identity type for IKE negotiations. Possible values are {@link
         * #ID_TYPE_FQDN}, {@link #ID_TYPE_RFC822_ADDR}, {@link #ID_TYPE_KEY_ID}

variables.name: KEY_ADD_KE_TO_CHILD_SESSION_REKEY_BOOL
variables.comment: Controls if KE payload should be added during child session local rekey procedure.

variables.name: KEY_EPDG_PCO_ID_IPV6_INT
variables.comment: Specifies the PCO id for IPv6 Epdg server address

variables.name: KEY_EPDG_PCO_ID_IPV4_INT
variables.comment: Specifies the PCO id for IPv4 Epdg server address

variables.name: KEY_SUPPORTS_EAP_AKA_FAST_REAUTH_BOOL
variables.comment: Controls if the IKE tunnel setup supports EAP-AKA fast reauth

variables.name: KEY_EPDG_ADDRESS_IP_TYPE_PREFERENCE_INT
AUTHENTICATION_METHOD_EAP_ONLY
variables.comment: * Certificate sent from the server is ignored. Only Extensible Authentication Protocol * (EAP) is used to authenticate the server. EAP_ONLY_AUTH payload is added to IKE_AUTH * request if supported. * * @see RFC 5998

variables.name: AUTHENTICATION_METHOD_CERT
variables.comment: Server is authenticated using its certificate.

variables.name: EPDG_ADDRESS_STATIC
variables.comment: Use static epdg address.

variables.name: EPDG_ADDRESS_PLMN
variables.comment: Construct the epdg address using plmn.

variables.name: EPDG_ADDRESS_PCO
variables.comment: * Use the epdg address received in protocol configuration options (PCO) from the network.

variables.name: EPDG_ADDRESS_CELLULAR_LOC
variables.comment: Use cellular location to chose epdg server

variables.name: EPDG_ADDRESS_VISITED_COUNTRY
variables.comment: Use Visited Country FQDN rule

variables.name: EPDG_PLMN_RPLMN
variables.comment:
* Use the Registered PLMN
         * @hide

variables.name: EPDG_PLMN_HPLMN
variables.comment:
* Use the PLMN derived from IMSI
         * @hide

variables.name: EPDG_PLMN_EHPLMN_ALL
variables.comment:
* Use all EHPLMN from SIM EF files
         * @hide

variables.name: EPDG_PLMN_EHPLMN_FIRST
variables.comment:
* Use the first EHPLMN from SIM EF files
         * @hide

variables.name: ID_TYPE_FQDN
variables.comment: * Ike Identification Fully Qualified Domain Name * * @see RFC 7296, Internet Key * Exchange Protocol Version 2 (IKEv2)

variables.name: ID_TYPE_RFC822_ADDR
variables.comment: * Ike Identification Fully Qualified RFC 822 email address. * * @see RFC 7296, Internet Key * Exchange Protocol Version 2 (IKEv2)

variables.name: ID_TYPE_KEY_ID
variables.comment: * Ike Identification opaque octet stream for vendor specific information * * @see RFC 7296, Internet Key * Exchange Protocol Version 2 (IKEv2)

variables.name: EPDG_ADDRESS_IPV4_PREFERRED
variables.comment: Prioritize IPv4 ePDG addresses.

variables.name: EPDG_ADDRESS_IPV6_PREFERRED
variables.comment: Prioritize IPv6 ePDG addresses

variables.name: EPDG_ADDRESS_IPV4_ONLY
variables.comment: Use IPv4 ePDG addresses only.

variables.name: EPDG_ADDRESS_IPV6_ONLY
variables.comment:
Use IPv6 ePDG addresses only.
         * @hide

variables.name: EPDG_ADDRESS_SYSTEM_PREFERRED
variables.comment: Follow the priority from DNS resolution results, which are sorted by using RFC6724 * algorithm. * * @see RFC 6724, Default Address * Selection for Internet Protocol Version 6 (IPv6) * @hide
